<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;SCP-005-J-EX&nbsp;Spoilers&nbsp;etc</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;collapse</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Spoiler - yes, this is just me writing an explanation of an &quot;Explained&quot; &quot;Joke&quot; SCP about explaining jokes. Yes, that makes me very annoying, and I should stop.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Apart from the punchline of the article, the levels of meta involved were not deliberate, but I definitely enjoyed reading people explain it to one another in the comments.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The other &quot;jokes&quot; referred to in the test logs are of course:
<ul>
<li style="list-style: none; display: inline">
<ul>
<li>&quot;A duck walks into a bar, and says 'Put it on my bill'&quot; - or one of the variations on that set-up.</li>
<li>&quot;Knock knock&quot; &#8230; &quot;Don't cry, it's only a ghost.&quot;</li>
<li>Pick your favourite racist stereotype.</li>
<li>Not a joke per se, but the standard &quot;anecdote falls flat without hilarious drunken context&quot;.</li>
<li>&quot;To get to the other side.&quot;</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
